results.name: Fang Gang
results.description:
Fang Gang is a collection of 8888 randomly assembled Fangsters - twisted lunatics that come out at night to throw parties, hang around in dark alleys and have fun on the streets of New Fang City.

You can find PxlFangs, our free mint collection for holders, [here](https://opensea.io/collection/pxlfangs).

results.name: Neon Junkies
results.description: Welcome to Neon City, a bustling cyberpunk metropolis infested with Neon Junkies - depraved citizens that scour the streets in search of their next fix.  Now you can explore the Ciphersquares universe with 10,000 characters specifically created with varying rarity traits.

results.name: Lil Devils
results.description: The Lil Devils is a collection of 6666 cute avatars stored as an ERC - 721 token on the Ethereum blockchain and hosted on IPFS.All 6666 devils are programmatically generated from over 160 unique traits.The collection contains four additional rare species.Each species has its own unique combination of traits.

results.name: Lockdown Lemmings
results.description:
10,000 adorable Lemmings, in need of your love and affection. Adopt one to join our community and raise awareness & money for mental health.

The vision of Lockdown Lemmings is to celebrate NFTs, and the way in which collectors follow one another, just like lemmings do.

You're already a Lemming at heart, so re-tweet and come join the pack!

results.name: Non-Fungible Forks #ForkHunger
results.description:
Ryan (dad/dev) + Anna (daughter/artiste) are generating 5,555 forks as NFTs to celebrate the London Fork. Pay what you want to mint one and we'll give it away.

Anyone who makes a copy of this collection is a forkhead. If you notice prices that are not in ETH (i.e. if they're pink instead of black ETH symbols), then it's a fake. These fakers seem to copy the text verbatim, so hopefully they'll copy this too.

Check Twitter and Discord for updates and increased utility for your forks!

Official OpenSea: https://opensea.io/assets/nonfungibleforks
Twitter: https://twitter.com/ForkHungerNFT
Discord: https://discord.gg/7HqTa9KMha

results.name: PxlFangs
results.description:
PxlFangs is a collection of 8888 randomly assembled pixelated Fangsters. After [Fang Runner](https://www.fanggang.io/fangrunnergame/) was released, every Fangster in the city got addicted to it. Then one day they were all sucked into the game, creating 32px versions of them called PxlFangsters.

This is a free mint collection made in collab with [pxlhns](https://opensea.io/pixelhans) for [Fang Gang](https://opensea.io/collection/fanggangnft) holders. You can find a Fangster ID checker on the [website](https://fanggang.io/pxlfangs/) to see if a Fangster can still claim a PxlFangster.

PxlFangsters are originally minted in 32x32 format, and now you can upgrade them to 48x48 Super PxlFangsters by using a Super PxlChip, an item purchasable in [New Fang City](https://newfangcity.com) or on secondary market through the [Awoo Items](https://opensea.io/collection/awooitems) collection.

results.name: ScaredyCat
results.description:
The Scaredy Cats were scared to DEATH of the metaverse bears. Help resurrect 3333 of them to the Ethereum blockchain.

Open if you dare.
Each Scaredy Cat will have their very own pet! Pets can be combined into Scaredy CAT NFT.

results.name: Bit Monsters NFT
results.description:
6666 Bit Monsters randomly generated and stored 100% on the Ethereum Blockchain

In the year 6666, the world is on the brink of collapse. 
Tensions between the two global powers spill over, and the Atomicans war arrives.
The glow from first bombs light up the Halloween sky. The survivors of the initial blast are left disfigured in their costumes. Humanity is lost, and the Bit Monsters rise from the ashes as evolutions next derivative.

results.name: BladeRunnerPunks
results.description:
The new generation of punk NFTs hit the Ethereum blockchain. 

10,000 unique dystopian NFTs with 100% CC0 to holders, newly constructed from scratch from over 100 traits to a defined BladeRunnerPunk-DNA rarity system. Forward facing and drawing eye-to-eye contact, BladeRunnerPunks emanate strong identity, status, & confidence. Inspired by the greatest sci-fi movie of all time and the greatest punk NFT collection! 

Look out for two new classes of punks:
- 5 Replicants (Mythical) 
- 124 Androids (Legendary) 

The future is wilder than we imagine. 

Note: BladeRunnerPunks are not associated with Alcon Entertainment.

results.name: BLU3PRINTS
results.description:
1,489 forgotten BLU3PRINTS were found, left behind by a distant civilization.

A free drop from @abwagmi with a unique Sybil-resistant allowlist method.

Traits generated on-chain, and BLU3PRINTS art is permanently mirrored in the contract.

Owners can swap between portrait and landscape orientation at will. Each piece in the collection implicitly comes with both orientations.
